Rollup understands whether or not a constructor function has side-effects, and [can remove `new` expressions if there are none](http://rollupjs.org/#%7B%22options%22%3A%7B%22format%22%3A%22cjs%22%2C%22moduleName%22%3A%22myBundle%22%2C%22globals%22%3A%7B%7D%7D%2C%22modules%22%3A%5B%7B%22name%22%3A%22main.js%22%2C%22code%22%3A%22function%20Foo%20%28%29%20%7B%5Cn%20%20%2F%2F%20comment%20out%20the%20next%20line%20%E2%80%93%20everything%20will%20be%20removed%5Cn%20%20alert%28%20'side-effect!'%20%29%3B%5Cn%7D%5Cnvar%20foo%20%3D%20new%20Foo%28%29%3B%22%7D%5D%7D):

``` js
function Foo () {
  // comment out the next line ‚Äì everything will be removed
  alert( 'side-effect!' );
}
var foo = new Foo();
```

But it [doesn't know about classes and constructors](http://rollupjs.org/#%7B%22options%22%3A%7B%22format%22%3A%22cjs%22%2C%22moduleName%22%3A%22myBundle%22%2C%22globals%22%3A%7B%7D%7D%2C%22modules%22%3A%5B%7B%22name%22%3A%22main.js%22%2C%22code%22%3A%22class%20Foo%20%7B%5Cn%20%20constructor%20%28%29%20%7B%5Cn%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20comment%20out%20the%20next%20line%20%E2%80%93%20has%20no%20effect%5Cn%20%20%20%20alert%28%20'side-effect!'%20%29%3B%5Cn%20%20%7D%5Cn%7D%5Cnvar%20foo%20%3D%20new%20Foo%28%29%3B%22%7D%5D%7D). I think that's something we could probably fix üëç
